    {
      "name": "Ориентир",
      "text": "A few steps from Wall Street, on Bowling Green, a bronze bull lowers its head and digs in as if the next second will be a charge. Charging Bull is both a landmark and shorthand: in one silhouette, it compresses the market's favourite story — risk, momentum, stubborn confidence. People don't come here for art history; they come for a ritual, a photo, a touch for luck, as if optimism could be made physical.",
