    {
      "name": "Разлёт · секции",
      "text": "You can't cast a thing this size as a single piece — no foundry's kiln takes three tonnes of molten metal in one pour. So Arturo Di Modica cast it in sections at Bedi-Makky Art Foundry in Greenpoint, Brooklyn, then welded and hand-finished the seams until the joints read as skin. Pulled apart, the sections show how the bull was actually built.",
