    {
      "name": "Морда и рога",
      "text": "Head-on, the bull is one of the city’s most photographed corners. There’s almost always a small crowd here: palms on the muzzle, business cards pressed to the horns, a quick rub for luck before the next photo. The nose and the tips of the horns are noticeably lighter than the rest of the body — patina worn away by years of touch, a place of power for people who hope a little of the animal’s momentum rubs off in return.",
